original: Briving, Carl-Eric Algot, tandläkare, Mellerud, f. 13/11/08 i Linköp. av stat :mäst, Algot B. o. Maria Enroth. G. 36 m. Aina Kempe. Barn: Göran f. 38, Karin 40, Ulla 44. — Stud:ex. v. Gbgs h. latin 29, med. stud. v. Lunds univ. o. Karol. inst. 29-31, tand-l:kand. 32, tandläk. 35. Assist, i Bengtsfors 35, praktik i Mellerud ’sed. s. å.
translated: Briving, Carl-Eric Algot was a dentist from Mellerud. He was born on November 13, 1908 in Linköping to parents Algot B. and Maria Enroth. In 1936, he married Aina Kempe and had three children: Göran (born in 1938), Karin (born in 1940), and Ulla (born in 1944). Briving graduated from Gothenburg's upper secondary school with a Latin focus in 1929, attended medical school at Lund University and the Karolinska Institute from 1929 to 1931, and received his dental degree in 1935. He worked as an assistant in Bengtsfors in 1935 and began practicing in Mellerud later that year.
